选择正确的公司法律架构 当你开始一个新生意时，一个最重要的决定就是选择公司的架构。你的选择会依据生意的类型和大小，个人的情况以及你计划怎样发展业务。你的选择可能会影响到税务责任，潜在的个人责任，资产保护以及你作为企业主的责任甚至更多。 这个讲座会深入讨论纽约州各种公司架构的利弊，例如个人所有型的公司，合伙公司，“c”或“s”型公司，以及有限责任公司（LLC），根据这些信息你可以决定哪种公司架构最适合自己。
longest_value: Interested in a paid apprenticeship and a career as a Line Cook in a restaurant kitchen? Attend a First Course NYC Info Session.First Course NYC is a new, 14-week culinary training program that will provide qualified New Yorkers access to entry-level Line Cook jobs and clear pathways to advancement and higher wages in respected NYC restaurants. In the first eight weeks of classroom kitchen training, participants will learn the fundamental culinary and job skills required to be an entry-level professional line cook. The training will be delivered at the Food Arts Center, a state-of-the-art kitchen training facility in midtown Manhattan. Participants will be paid a weekly stipend of $125/week during the initial eight-week training, and will receive weekly metrocards and daily meals.The remaining six weeks of the program will offer an on-the-job apprenticeship in respected NYC restaurant kitchens at a rate of $16/hr. It is intended that qualified apprentices who successfully complete their training will continue with their employer as a full time entry-level line cook. Eligible Candidates must:Be at least 18 years of ageBe a New York City residentBe authorized to work in the United StatesBe able to lift up to 40 poundsBe able and willing to work flexible hours, including evenings, weekends, and holidaysDemonstrate a strong interest in, and enthusiasm for, food and for work in a restaurant kitchenIf this sounds like a good opportunity for you, register for ONE of the following info sessions:Brooklyn Workforce1 Career Center: 9 Bond St 5th Floor, Brooklyn, NY 11201Tuesday, October 1: 10 – 11:30 a.m. ETFriday, October 4: 1 – 2:30 p.m. ETTuesday, October 8: 3 – 4:30 p.m. ET Friday, October 11: 10 – 11:30 a.m. ET         Tuesday, October 15: 9 – 10:30 a.m. ETFriday, October 18: 1 – 2:30 p.m. ET  Upper Manhattan Workforce1 Career Center: 215 W 125th St 6th Floor, New York, NY 10027Monday, September 30: 9 – 10:30 a.m. ETMonday, September 30: 3 – 4 p.m. ETMonday, October 7: 9 – 10:30 a.m. ETMonday, October 7: 3 – 4:30 p.m. ETMonday, October 21: 9 – 10:30 a.m. ETMonday, October 21: 3 – 4:30 p.m. ET

QuickBooks Learn the key features and benefits of this accounting software!Business owners need to monitor their spending and expenses in order to maintain a healthy profit. QuickBooks can help you keep track of daily transactions, as well as develop financial reports such as Income Statements, Balance Sheets, and Cash Flow Statements. This course will teach you how this software program can help you track your business financials effectively and efficiently. You will learn about:Setting up your chart of accountsRecording purchases, bills and accounts payableRecording your sales, receive payments and make depositsCreating reports that help you understand business performancePlease note, this course is designed to teach businesses how to use the software application. In order to benefit from this course, you must have a basic knowledge of business financials and computer applications.  If you are not familiar with concepts such as: categorizing revenues and expenses on an income statement, using a balance sheet, creating and using a cash flow statement, and accounting and bookkeeping methodology, you should register for Small Business Financing or Show Me The Money: Financial Statements & Profit as a pre-requisiteThe Queens BSC will accept EventBrite course reservations and hold a seat for all registrants, however that does not guarantee admittance into the class. Upon submission of your registration, a staff member will reach out to you and provide an application for this class. Once an application is submitted the Queens BSC, we will conduct a phone interview at which point you will be advised of your acceptance into the class and confirm securing your seat.

Neighborhood 360° Fellows help community-based development organizations complete commercial revitalization projects and connect local stakeholders to City resources. Fellows are paid by SBS and are full-time community development professionals. Through the program, SBS aims to build a network of leaders prepared with commercial revitalization expertise and experience in New York City neighborhoods.  SBS is now accepting applications for 2020-2021 host site organizations. We are looking for Host Sites that meet these minimum criteria:Nonprofit community-based development organization (Business Improvement Districts, local development corporations, merchants associations, and other organizations) operating in New York City and incorporated in New York StateAble to assist in recruiting candidates and interviewing finalist fellow applicantsAble to provide the fellow with a desk and supporting equipment (i.e. computer and access to organization's phone)During the webinar, participating community-based organizations will gain:An overview of the Neighborhood 360° Fellows program and expectations of host site organizationsExamples of projects conducted by previous cohortsA detailed walk-through of the application process and selection timelineWho should attend:Senior staff and board members of NYC Business Improvement Districts, Chambers of Commerce, Merchants Associations, and other community-based organizationsInformation on how to access the webinar will be sent out to those who RSVP.Learn more about the Neighborhood 360° Fellows program here.
